{
  "texts": [
    "For instance, in pulse-width modulation (PWM) schemes, inputs are codified in different pulse widths (0 s, T READ /256 s, 2•T READ / 256 s, etc. until T READ).",
    "This allows overcoming device non-linearity but suffers from low throughput 57.",
    "Alternatively, in the so-called bit-serial encoding 97 approaches, high-resolution crossbar inputs are presented as a stream of voltage pulses with constant amplitude and width 48,56.",
    "For example, to represent 16-bit crossbar inputs, m-bit voltage signals are streamed to the crossbar row over 16/m time cycles 98.",
    "After VMM calculation, the partial products (the outputs of each time step) are accumulated together to form the final output value."
  ]
}